On 11/15/04 7:56 PM, "Steve Pribyl" <steve(-at-)unliketea.com> wrote:

> I want to get a 4 point lug wrench but don't know if I need metric or
> english.

19mm. Be sure to get the 4-point kind. The nuts are often torque beyond the
94 ft. lbs spec and getting them off with the 1-arm kind can be hard even
when torqued to spec. Even with the 4-arm I often use a floor jack handle to
make light work of removal.

Search Craftsman.com for 47402.

